%N A394290 Number of partitions of n such that the multiplicity m of the greatest part g is a part of the partition and m < g.
%H A394290 Seiichi Manyama, <a href="/A394290/b394290.txt">Table of n, a(n) for n = 1..1000</a>
%F A394290 G.f.: Sum_{j>=1} Sum_{k=1..j-1} q^((j+1)*k) / Product_{k=1..j-1} (1-q^k).
%e A394290 a(8) counts these 12 partitions: 71, 611, 521, 5111, 431, 4211, 41111, 332, 3221, 32111, 311111, 2111111.
%o A394290 (PARI) my(N=50, q='q+O('q^N)); concat([0, 0], Vec(sum(j=1, N, sum(k=1, j-1, q^((j+1)*k))/prod(k=1, j-1, 1-q^k))))
